  </element>
  <element>
    <id>UMLNote</id>
    <coordinates>
      <x>960</x>
      <y>50</y>
      <w>510</w>
      <h>520</h>
    </coordinates>
    <panel_attributes>bg=gray
fontsize=16
InputDifferenceJoysticks: must export store the result of 
inputs on tick, but only when joysick is connected. it's ticking 
is enabled and disabled while a binding is being set.

React is the UI for setting a binding, removing an old joy, ignoring
a newly connected joy, or swapping joys.

joy cookie stores a delimited string containing the joy names in
order of the joy ids. 

Bindings exist for all Flight Axes, always stores flight axis,
if it's Joy is set, it returns an id, and has an axisId,
tick uses the axisValue to set the flight axis.

When you connect a joy, if the set name from cookies matches, 
sets the id for that joy, if the id does not match the cookies,
it may Swap joy may need to happen for the bindings and joys.
If no name match, checks if an unnamed 
slot, if not tells React to ask to delete  a joy, or ignore the new 
one. if there is an unnamed slot, sets the joy name and id. 
After a joy changes, the joys array is re-ordered.
Cookies are updated whenever a joy or binding changes.

A binding may not have a joy, a joy is set when the binding is set.
A binding may have an unenabled joy, it becomes enabled when the joy
is connected.</panel_attributes>
